<item>
            <title>[JCR-22] DefaultItemStateProvider contains grow-only cache</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/JCR-22</link>
                <project id="10591" key="JCR">Jackrabbit Content Repository</project>
                        <description>The DefaultItemStateProvider class contains a private HashMap &amp;quot;items&amp;quot; which contains references to ItemState objects. The bad thing about this cache is, that it only grows, but is not being managed to forget about &amp;quot;unused&amp;quot; items.&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;
Example: A repository which is filled with 9350 nodes and 52813 properties grows this items map to 1&amp;#39;667&amp;#39;557 (!) entries. In this concrete case, the VM all13ates 213MB to the heap of which 57MB is referenced by the DefaultItemStateProvider.items map.</description>
                <environment>Jackrabbit SVN 106295</environment>
